communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Iowa Open Records Law, I am hereby requesting the same records requested by Jason Koebler regarding the Iowa Capitol holiday display.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rachel Janes

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Iowa Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

• Any communications, memos, emails, letters, text messages,  voice recordings, voice messages, and phone call recordings regarding the Satanic holiday display at the State Capitol, as well as
attachments
• Any communications, memos, emails, letters, text messages,  voice recordings, voice messages, and phone call recordings regarding Governor Reynolds' statement(s) regarding the Satanic holiday display at the State Capitol, as well as
attachments
• Any communications, memos, emails, text messages, or letters between the agency and members
of the Satanic Temple
• Any communications, memos, emails, text messages, or letters about members
of the Satanic Temple
• Any communications, memos, emails, letters, text messages,  voice recordings, and phone call recordings that mention "Satanic Temple"
• The application and approval process documents related to the Satanic Temple's
display or The Satanic Temple Iowa's display
• Any communications regarding the application and approval of the Satanic Temple's
display or The Satanic Temple Iowa's display
• Any internal guidelines or policies referenced in the decision to permit the display
• Any communications to or from Michael Cassidy
• Any communications that mention Michael Cassidy
• Any communications to or from R. Davis Younts
• Any communications that mention R. Davis Younts
• Any communications to or from Sara Pasquale
• Any communications that mention Sara Pasquale

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rachel Janes
